               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18381126-name-1414" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18381126-name-1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381126-name-1414" type="surname" value="TICK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381126-name-1414" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN TICK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a fishmonger, living at Greenwich. On the 3rd of November I saw the prisoner near my stall, in Beer-lane, Greenwich—I sent him on errands—he behaved with the greatest propriety from Friday till Saturday—on Sunday, when I came home to dinner my wife asked me if I had taken a bag out of the drawer containing 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I said no—I then sent for the prisoner—he came, and I accused him of it—he said he did not touch it—he said, "Why should I rob you, when you behaved so well to me?"—I then put it into the policeman's hands, and he asked him why he should rob this poor man, after he behaved so well to him—he asked him several questions, and then the prisoner got up, went to the balustrade of the square, and pulled out a purse containing 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., which was part of my money.</p>
